id: pm-qmx3
title: 2026-05-30 package SDK dogfood audit and startup telemetry performance pass
description: "Manual audit and remediation pass for package-first pm ecosystem, SDK/public runtime contracts, calendar/search dogfood, token-optimized agent UX, live telemetry/Sentry health, and startup responsiveness after the latest main changes."
type: Task
status: closed
priority: 0
tags[7]: agents,audit,dogfood,package-first,performance,sdk,telemetry
created_at: "2026-05-30T06:05:18.203Z"
updated_at: "2026-05-30T06:49:50.137Z"
author: maintainer-agent
parent: pm-59gj
resolution: Telemetry startup overhead reduced by adding a cross-process flush spawn gate; tracked metadata collection runtime cache removed from git and ignored; package SDK/calendar/search ecosystem audit completed with no additional code defects requiring this slice.
expected_result: "pm package-first SDK, calendar, search, telemetry, Sentry, docs/skills, static quality, typecheck, version policy, secret scan, npx smoke, compatibility, npm pack, and semantic qwen dogfood pass after the latest package changes."
actual_result: "Final sandbox-safe pm linked test run passed 9/9, full release gate passed with 2008 coverage tests at 100 percent, required Sentry/telemetry gate passed with Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry error rate 1.48 percent, direct package-owned changelog check passed unchanged."
comments[15]{created_at,author,text}:
  "2026-05-30T06:05:18.203Z",maintainer-agent,"Duplicate-check evidence: bootstrap passed; pm context showed only open pm-59gj and pm-3mal; pm search for broad audit SDK packages calendar telemetry semantic search performance agent UX found closed broad-audit lineage pm-rnpb plus open pm-59gj and open claimed pm-3mal. No duplicate current audit child exists, so this task is created under pm-59gj for the 2026-05-30 manual dogfood/remediation pass. GitHub preflight found no open issues or PRs, no open Dependabot alerts, no pm-cli notifications, and code scanning is unavailable with current gh token scope."
  "2026-05-30T06:05:41.858Z",maintainer-agent,"Plan: (1) run isolated temp-project dogfood for init --with-packages, package catalog/doctor/upgrade, SDK imports/runtime contracts, calendar, search/reindex, plan lifecycle, linked files/docs/tests, health/validate; (2) inspect live telemetry/Sentry and current GitHub runs, keeping host-specific notes in ignored scripts/prod/telemetry; (3) profile command hot paths and review open pm-3mal performance scope without forcing ownership; (4) implement only concrete high-impact fixes found; (5) link files/tests/docs, run focused gates plus release gate, then PR with 15-minute bot review window."
  "2026-05-30T06:08:36.451Z",maintainer-agent,"Dogfood evidence: isolated package-first dogfood passed with PM_DOGFOOD_SEMANTIC=1 and qwen3-embedding:0.6b. It exercised 86 commands across init --with-packages, package install/catalog/doctor/upgrade, SDK/runtime contracts, calendar, search/reindex, Plan lifecycle, linked files/docs/tests, health/validate, and release. Slowest expected linked-test run was 3094ms; semantic hybrid reindex was 1038ms; slowest non-test/non-semantic surfaces were plan show deep 525ms, package install all 476ms, package local install 474ms, claim 424ms, plan approve 404ms, package list 380ms."
  "2026-05-30T06:15:23.670Z",maintainer-agent,"Implementation evidence: fixed two audit findings. First, removed tracked runtime cache .agents/pm/runtime/metadata-cache-collections.json from the git index and added it to .gitignore alongside the other metadata/body/history/telemetry runtime caches, leaving the local cache ignored. Second, added a cross-process telemetry flush spawn gate so command_start and command_finish do not both pay detached child startup while a flush child is already booting or a process flush lock is active. Focused telemetry regression passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/telemetry-flush-spawn.spec.ts tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts (20 tests)."
  "2026-05-30T06:15:30.340Z",maintainer-agent,"Observability evidence: live required Sentry/telemetry gate passed with Sentry checked=true critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry finish_error_rate_pct=1.49 missing_error_code_rows=0 over 7 days. Remote stack health passed: telemetry API version 2026.5.29 healthy, Grafana reachable, RabbitMQ pm.telemetry.events depth 0 with 1 consumer, worker/container stack up, and Postgres recorded 9434 events in the last 24h. Direct sentry issue list for unresolved pm-cli issues returned none. Timing smoke after the telemetry spawn gate averaged: pm --version 81ms, list-open 297ms, get --fields 257ms, package list compact fields 268ms with telemetry enabled."
  "2026-05-30T06:17:23.662Z",maintainer-agent,"Correction: telemetry spawn-gate regression coverage was folded into existing tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts to keep tests/unit under the static-quality directory-load threshold. Current focused command is node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts."
  "2026-05-30T06:19:38.991Z",maintainer-agent,"Dependency/SDK audit evidence: pnpm audit --prod --json and pnpm audit --json both reported 0 vulnerabilities. pnpm outdated --format json reports commander 15.0.0 is newer than current 14.0.3, but npm metadata shows commander@15 requires node >=22.12.0 while pm-cli still supports node >=20, so this pass intentionally does not raise the CLI engine floor for a dependency-major update. SDK smoke passed against dist/sdk/index.js for defineExtension, getContracts, getWorkspaceContracts, runCalendar, renderCalendarMarkdown, and PM_CORE_COMMAND_NAMES; package catalog compact fields reported all 8 bundled package aliases."
  "2026-05-30T06:25:37.227Z",maintainer-agent,"Full release-gate evidence: node scripts/release/run-gates.mjs --json --telemetry-mode required --max-sentry-critical 10 --max-sentry-high 20 --max-telemetry-error-rate 10 --max-telemetry-missing-error-rows 0 passed. Checks passed: build, typecheck, docs/skills, static quality, coverage (2008 tests, 100 percent statements/branches/functions/lines), version policy, secret scan, npx smoke, package-first dogfood, npm pack dry run, compatibility check, and required Sentry/telemetry gate with Sentry critical=0 high=0 total=0 and telemetry error rate 1.49 percent missing_error_code_rows=0."
  "2026-05-30T06:26:07.127Z",maintainer-agent,"Changelog evidence: package-owned pnpm changelog:pm ran through pm-changelog and reported CHANGELOG.md unchanged; pnpm changelog:pm:check also passed with item_count=870. No manual changelog edits were made."
  "2026-05-30T06:31:13.793Z",maintainer-agent,"Linked-test harness note: a pm test run showed pnpm changelog:pm:check fails under the default schema-only sandbox because it compares the real CHANGELOG.md against an empty seeded tracker. The standalone real-repo check had already passed. I am updating that linked test to pm_context_mode=tracker so future linked runs verify the real tracker-shaped changelog state instead of the empty schema sandbox."
  "2026-05-30T06:36:57.220Z",maintainer-agent,"Linked-test decision: removed pnpm changelog:pm:check from sandboxed linked tests. The command is package-owned and passed directly in the real repo, but it is not safe as a pm linked test because the harness redirects PM_PATH/PM_GLOBAL_PATH while the script compares the real workspace CHANGELOG.md. Keeping it as explicit direct evidence avoids a false failing test and preserves the no-real-tracker-write rule for linked tests."
  "2026-05-30T06:41:29.587Z",maintainer-agent,"Final linked-test evidence: pm test pm-qmx3 --run --progress passed after removing the non-sandbox-safe changelog check from linked tests. Final run executed 9 sandbox-safe commands successfully: secret scan, full release gate, required Sentry/telemetry gate, focused telemetry runtime test, semantic qwen package-first dogfood, docs/skills gate, static quality gate, typecheck, and version policy."
  "2026-05-30T06:43:35.455Z",maintainer-agent,"Final changelog evidence after close: pnpm changelog:pm regenerated CHANGELOG.md with item_count=871 after pm-qmx3 closed, using installed pm-changelog@2026.5.30; pnpm changelog:pm:check then passed unchanged. The project-managed pm-changelog extension metadata/runtime were refreshed to 2026.5.30 and linked to this item."
  "2026-05-30T06:44:11.525Z",maintainer-agent,"Pre-commit safety evidence: final pnpm changelog:pm:check passed unchanged after linking package/changelog files; node scripts/check-secrets.mjs passed; pnpm quality:static passed; git diff --check passed; pm list-in-progress returned count=0."
  "2026-05-30T06:49:50.137Z",maintainer-agent,"PR review follow-up evidence: addressed Sourcery/Gemini feedback on PR #84. acquireTelemetryFlushSpawnGate now avoids stale-lock removal unless a stale spawn lock exists, avoids recursive parent creation unless direct lock mkdir returns ENOENT, and fails closed on unexpected filesystem errors. Tests now reuse _testOnly lock path helpers and cover spawn-gate cleanup when the process flush lock is already held. Verification passed: node scripts/run-tests.mjs test -- tests/unit/telemetry-runtime.spec.ts (21 tests), pnpm typecheck, pnpm quality:static, node scripts/check-secrets.mjs, pnpm changelog:pm:check, git diff --check."
